page.title: 16GARB. LISTED BUILDINGS.
page.content: 37TH LIST OF BUILDINGS OF INTEREST. {ST.JOHN THE BAPTIST CHURCH.}13th,14th, 15th Century,restored 1862 Grade 1. {ALL SAINTS CHURCH (Ruin).}Late 14th, demolished 1734.Ancient Mon. Grade 2. {PEAR TREE COTTAGE and COMPTON,}early 18th Century. Grade 2. {JACQUES HALL HSE.}15th,17th Century altered 18th Century. Grade 2*. {MULBERRY COTTAGE.}Early 18th.Grade 2. {BRECKLAND HOUSE.}Late 15th. Grade 2. {POST MILL, c1780.}No sails. Grade 2*. {FOX INN,}Mid 18th Century. Grade 2. {Gothic House.}Early 19th. GRADE 2. {THE GRANGE.}Early 17th, altered 20th Century. Grade 2. In village,just North of the grid ref. area are remaining parts of{THE MANOR. ie. Service wing,stables,laundry cott. coachman's house, Old Manor,Manor Cott.,West Gateway. Also{Stubbing's & {Edward's Farmhouses,}all Grade 2.
